The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, December 18, 2003 				 Ontrack facilitates online bidding
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Dec. 17: City-based Ontrack Systems has launched the countrys first electronic tendering platform.																								East Central Railway has already issued three tender notices along with bid documents for online hosting. Prospective bidders can have direct access to the railway tender documents and can submit bids online along with digital certificates after making necessary money deposits through an integrated payment gateway.																								Ontrack managing director B. Hari said, The solution framework is public key infrastructure (PKI) enabled and tendertimes can now issue class II digital certificates to bidders, authorities and general public through their partnership with SafeScrypt.																								The Railway Board has recommended that divisions go in for onjline high value tenders of around Rs 40 crore.
